4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would establish the Guardianship Bill
6 of Rights to provide adults with guardians certain
7 rights relating to access to justice, core human
8 rights, and decision-making.
9
10
11 A BILL
12 TO BE ENTITLED
13 AN ACT
14
15 Relating to adults with guardians; to establish the
16 Guardianship Bill of Rights; to provide adults with guardians
17 certain rights relating to access to justice, core human
18 rights, and decision-making.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
20 Section 1. (a) This section shall be known and may be
21 cited as the Guardianship Bill of Rights.
22 (b) For the purposes of this section, the following
23 terms have the following meanings:
24 (1) ADULT. An individual who has reached the age of
25 majority pursuant to Section 26-1-1, Code of Alabama 1975.
26 (2) GUARDIAN. The same meaning as Section 26-2A-20,
27 Code of Alabama 1975.
28 (c) Each adult with a guardian has the right to access
Page 1

(c) Each adult with a guardian has the right to access
HB99 INTRODUCED
29 justice, which includes the right of each adult with a
30 guardian to:
31 (1) Maintain all rights that the court has not granted
32 to the adult's guardian;
33 (2) A lawyer who advocates for the outcome that the
34 adult desires;
35 (3) Be present and participate in all court hearings
36 relating to the adult;
37 (4) Inform the court of the adult's concerns or
38 complaints about the adult's guardianship or guardian;
39 (5) Ask the court to review whether to change,
40 continue, or end the adult's guardianship and to review
41 whether the guardian is right for the adult;
42 (6) If there is a question about the adult's capacity
43 to exercise a specific right, have a qualified person evaluate
44 the adult's abilities and whether some or all of the adult's
45 rights should be restored;
46 (7) Support and accommodations as necessary to
47 effectively communicate with the court and to understand court
48 proceedings; and
49 (8) Have the adult's rights explained in the method of
50 communication and in the language that the adult chooses.
51 (d) Each adult with a guardian retains core human
52 rights, including the right of each adult with a guardian to:
53 (1) Be treated with dignity and respect;
54 (2) Be free from abuse, neglect, exploitation, and
55 discrimination;
56 (3) Remain as independent as possible;
Page 2

(3) Remain as independent as possible;
HB99 INTRODUCED
57 (4) Express and practice the adult's own religious
58 preferences;
59 (5) Personal privacy; and
60 (6) Humane, safe, and sanitary living, learning, and
61 working environments.
62 (e) Each adult with a guardian retains decision-making
63 rights, including the right to:
64 (1) A competent guardian who advocates for and respects
65 the adult's goals, needs, preferences, and desires, including
66 but not limited to those relating to medical treatment,
67 cultural practices, and religious beliefs;
68 (2) Fully participate in all decisions to the extent
69 that the adult desires to and is able to be involved,
70 especially those decisions affecting the adult's care, living
71 situation, activities, and social interactions;
72 (3) Receive necessary services and rehabilitation in
73 the least restrictive conditions, within available resources
74 and which protect the adult's personal privacy;
75 (4) Have the adult's guardian prudently manage the
76 adult's resources;
77 (5) Fully participate in decisions relating to the
78 management of the adult's property, to the extent that the
79 adult desires to and is able to be involved; and
80 (6) Keep confidential those matters that the adult
81 wishes to keep confidential, unless that information is
82 necessary to: (i) obtain services; (ii) prevent abuse,
83 neglect, or exploitation; or (iii) modify the adult's
84 guardianship order.
Page 3

guardianship order.
